        <Parent_String>lip-vibrated aerophones with conical bore: with fingerholes [300209195], lip-vibrated aerophones with conical bore [300195078], lip-vibrated aerophones [300041639], aerophones [300041622], sound devices by acoustical characteristics [300041621], sound devices (equipment) [300387677], Sound Devices (hierarchy name) [300041619], Furnishings and Equipment (hierarchy name) [300264551], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>European lip-vibrated aerophones of conical bore, consisting of a long wooden or ivory tube, straight or gently curved, with fingerholes, and made in three main sizes: treble, small treble, and tenor.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Aerófonos europeos que vibran con los labios y de diámetro interior cónico, consistentes en un largo tubo de madera o marfil, recto o ligeramente curvo, con orificios digitales, y construídos en tres tamaños principales: soprano, sopranino y tenor.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Blaasinstrumenten, sopraan-, sopranino- en tenorstemming, bestaande uit een lange houten of ivoren buis, conische boring, recht, ook licht gebogen, vingergaten; bespeeld door lipspanning; Europa.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052452/Encyclopedie van muziekinstrumenten (1977)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>歐洲的以嘴唇振動之圓錐形口徑管樂器，是由一具筆直或者是稍微有弧度的木製或者是象牙製的長型筒管所構成的，有著數個指孔，並且製作成三種主要的尺寸：高音(treble)、小高音(small treble)，以及次中音(tenor)。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052784/TELDAP database (2009-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Europäisches Lippenton-Aerofon mit langer konischer Röhre aus Holz oder Elfenbein, die gerade oder leicht gebogen ist, und mit Grifflöchern; hauptsächlich in drei Größen gefertigt: Diskantzink, kleiner Zink und großer Zink.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
